div.p:
Lanfrank Archbishop of Canterbury, calles
Lanf. epist. ad Hug. quae est apud Bar. an. 1080. nu. 27 Henry the fourth, though deposed by Pope Hildebrand, gloriosum Imperatorem, a glorious Emperour, and withall addes, that he could not obteine so great a victorie (against Rodulph) to whom the Pope had giuen the Empire) sine magno dei auxilio, without the great assistance of God;
whom yet the Bishop did not thinke to giue assistance to vniust causes.
